The bank says affected customers will be notified but has declined to comment further on the value of the goods stolen from a Randburg branch. JOHANNESBURG The First National Bank (FNB) branch in Randburg will remain closed indefinitely after it was robbed by a gang who made off with an undisclosed number of safety deposit boxes.The suspects held the branch s security guard hostage on Sunday and then used a grinder to chisel through a wall to gain access to the vault.The Hawks are investigating a case of business robbery and says it s unclear how many boxes were taken.FNB says affected customers will be notified but bank has declined to comment further on the value of the goods stolen.This customer says she wants to be compensated. There was basically all our jewellery and Kruger coins in the vault. It was probably worth over R300,000. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)